<subSubSection lastPageId="159" lastPageNumber="160" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 146" captionStartId="F146" captionText="Figure 146. Distribution of Conostegia colliculosa." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure146" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96504" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">146</figureCitation>
). Restricted to the Caribbean slope of Cost Rica and Panama, 150-650 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="973941" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure146" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96504" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" start="Figure 146" startId="F146">
<paragraph pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Figure 146.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia colliculosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="colliculosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Conostegia colliculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph lastPageId="159" lastPageNumber="160" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
This rare species was assigned to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ambyarrhena" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia subsp. section" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Ambyarrhena" species="colliculosa" subSpecies="section">Miconia section Ambyarrhena</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="239" pageNumber="240" pagination="33 - 54" refId="B6" refString="Almeda, F, 2000. New Costa Rican and Panamanian species of Miconia (Melastomataceae: Miconieae). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 52 (4): 33 - 54" title="New Costa Rican and Panamanian species of Miconia (Melastomataceae: Miconieae)." volume="52" year="2000">Almeda (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. The drawing in the protologue and study of the type specimen confirmed that the style 
<pageBreakToken pageId="159" pageNumber="160" start="start">is</pageBreakToken>
exserted and that the anthers are yellow, like most of its relatives, including 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="159" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="159" pageNumber="160">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subpeltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="159" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subpeltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="159" pageNumber="160">Conostegia subpeltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. With the latter two species it also shares an irregularly rupturing calyx but in the case of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia colliculosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="159" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="colliculosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="159" pageNumber="160">Conostegia colliculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lobes are thicker and the calyx teeth longer. In addition, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia colliculosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="159" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="colliculosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="159" pageNumber="160">Conostegia colliculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has five merous sessile flowers disposed in bracteate clusters whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="159" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="159" pageNumber="160">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subpeltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="159" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subpeltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="159" pageNumber="160">Conostegia subpeltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have four merous flowers that are not clustered in the inflorescences. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia supeltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="159" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="supeltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="159" pageNumber="160">Conostegia supeltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia colliculosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="159" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="colliculosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="159" pageNumber="160">Conostegia colliculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having subpeltate leaves and axillary inflorescences. 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="239" pageNumber="240" pagination="33 - 54" refId="B6" refString="Almeda, F, 2000. New Costa Rican and Panamanian species of Miconia (Melastomataceae: Miconieae). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 52 (4): 33 - 54" title="New Costa Rican and Panamanian species of Miconia (Melastomataceae: Miconieae)." volume="52" year="2000">Almeda (2000)</bibRefCitation>
suggested the relationship with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="159" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="159" pageNumber="160">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
